summary: hi! I’m a girl. I’m bisexual so it really doesn’t matter! I have curly brown hair and brown eyes. I’m relatively short. I’m...
question: hi! I’m a girl. I’m bisexual so it really doesn’t matter! I have curly brown hair and brown eyes. I’m relatively short. I’m kinda quiet when you first meet me, but I’m working on it and I’m generally more confident now. I’m not that outspoken unless it’s like injustice or bullying. I don’t do that. I’m really interested in the human mind and human behavior. I enjoy people and working with them. I don’t like feeling lonely. Can you ship me with someone from Marvel.  If you can’t I get it. Thanks!
answer:
I ship you with…

Marvel: Wanda Maximoff!

summary: My theory for why Harley is in Endgame: his mom and his sister both died in the snap. The avengers get back all the superheroes...
body:
My theory for why Harley is in Endgame: his mom and his sister both died in the snap. The avengers get back all the superheroes who died but they have to have a specific person in mind to bring them back so most of humanity is still dead. They go back in time to get all the infinity stones and use them in a new device that captain marvel uses. She spends weeks going through every recorded person in every government database to bring them back but she gives up and there are still millions left, including Harleys family. They get back to earth to find that Harley has been the sole protector of the entirety of america in his own customized iron man suit because crime rates are at an all time high since a lot of the law enforcement is dead. Also Kate Bishop was on a trip to Europe and had been the superhero there as Hawkeye. Tony hires them both as his second and third ever teenage interns and convinces captain marvel to at least bring back Harleys family. She gets back into the rhythm of it and spends a couple more days bringing back everyone. The world is saved again and Harley is Iron Lad and Kate Bishop is Hawkeye and everyone is happy

None of this is going to happen but it was fun to think about, for me at least

title: Across Time And Space
body:
read it on the AO3 at http://bit.ly/2X1Qz61

by Gwendal_Wincott

Everyone was born with soulmates, but some were born with two soulmates. One was a lover, the other was a best friend or a sibling. Sometimes soulmates hurt each other, but in the end they will always care for the one they were bonded to.

Soulmates are born for each other.

Having soulmates didn’t mean you’ll always be happy and content. But it did give you the hope that one day everything will work out. If other half of your soul cannot love you, then who can.

summary: Things wrong with Avengers: Infinity War Thanos killing half (or all) of the Asgardian refugees (especially after all the time...
body:
Things wrong with Avengers: Infinity War


Thanos killing half (or all) of the Asgardian refugees (especially after all the time Taika Waititi took to show the horrors of colonialism and imperialism and to promote refugees and immigrants).


Wanda (and the rest of the Avengers) being willing to risk half of the Universe against the life of a sentient toaster oven.


Captain America insisting that they don’t trade in lives and then asking the entire Wakandan army to lay down there lives for the chance of possibly, maybe saving the toaster oven.


The Wakandan army being slaughtered over one sentient toaster (I really can’t say this enough. I was appalled when I first watched it in the theater).


Thanos killing Gamora and the scene being framed in such a way that the audience is expected to feel sympathy for him.


The whole framing of Thanos plan to kill half the Universe as being the logical thing to do, if it’s not the moral thing to do, even though it’s without a doubt the stupidest plan in the history of stupid plans. And why didn’t anybody bother to point it out to him? Like just use the Gauntlet to make more resources!


Did I mention the Wakandans dying?


They didn’t use the Immigrant Song for Thor’s dramatic arrival when he started decimating the alien army. I mean I would have even settled for Thunderstruck by AC/DC


(i’m sure i forgot some so feel free to add on)
